Plastic pollution across the globe

Lets visualize plastic pollution across the globe First, lets look at the distribution of mean PVC plastics around the world.

world <- map_data("world") #creates a df of polygons of the world

plastics_world <- plastics %>% 
  select(country,pvc, hdpe, ldpe, pet, pp) %>% 
  group_by(country) %>% 
  summarise(mean_pvc = mean(pvc), 
            mean_hdpe = mean(hdpe),
            mean_ldpe = mean(ldpe), 
            mean_pet = mean(pet), 
            mean_pp = mean(pp)) %>% 
  rename(region = country)
view(plastics_world)

plastics_world <- plastics_world %>% 
  inner_join(world, 
             by = "region")
ggplot()+
  geom_polygon(data = world, 
               aes(x = long, 
                   y = lat, 
                   group = group), 
               colour = "black")+
  geom_polygon(data = plastics_world, 
               aes(x = long, 
                   y = lat,
                   group = group,
                   fill = mean_pvc))+
  scale_fill_viridis_c()+
  theme_minimal()+
  theme(panel.background = element_rect(fill = "light blue"))+
  coord_map(projection = "mercator", 
            xlim = c(-180, 180))+
  labs(title = "Mean PVC Plastic Count for Different Countries", 
       x = "Longitude", 
       y = "Latitude", 
       fill = "Mean PVC count")
